---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Case Study: How Pristine Detail Co. Built a Fully Booked Schedule | Lead Flow North">
  <article class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-8">
        <a href="/industries/auto-services/detailing" class="inline-flex items-center text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 font-medium">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path></svg>
          Back to Auto Detailing
        </a>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Article Header -->
      <header class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Case Study</span>
          <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">7 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          How Pristine Detail Co. Built a Fully Booked Schedule with 73% More Repeat Customers
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
          A Mississauga mobile detailer went from inconsistent bookings to a waitlist—all by automating his customer communication.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
          <span>February 2026</span>
          <span class="mx-3">•</span>
          <span>Lead Flow North Team</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Results Banner -->
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-cyan-600 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 text-white">
          <div class="text-center mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Results at a Glance</h2>
            <p class="text-blue-100">After 5 months with Lead Flow North</p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2">73%</div>
              <div class="text-blue-100">More Repeat Bookings</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2">82%</div>
              <div class="text-blue-100">Reduction in No-Shows</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2">4.9★</div>
              <div class="text-blue-100">Google Rating</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2">2 wks</div>
              <div class="text-blue-100">Booking Waitlist</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

          <!-- Client Overview -->
          <div class="bg-slate-100 p-6 rounded-xl my-8 not-prose">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Client Overview</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Business:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">Pristine Detail Co.</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Location:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">Mississauga, Ontario</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Type:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">Mobile auto detailing</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Services:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">Full detail, ceramic coating, PPF</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Team Size:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">Owner + 1 employee</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Engagement:</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white ml-2">5 months (ongoing)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">The Challenge</h2>

          <p>
            Jason Torres started Pristine Detail Co. in 2022 with a simple mission: bring exceptional mobile detailing to busy professionals who couldn't find time to drive to a shop. His work was exceptional—every car left looking showroom fresh.
          </p>

          <p>
            But his business was a constant struggle.
          </p>

          <p>
            "I'd have one week where I was working 12 hours a day, then the next week I'd have maybe two bookings," Jason explains. "I'd spend hours every day texting people trying to schedule appointments. Half the time they'd ghost me, or we'd finally set something up and then they wouldn't be home when I showed up."
          </p>

          <p>
            The numbers told the story:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>No-show rate:</strong> 23%</li>
            <li><strong>Repeat customer rate:</strong> 18%</li>
            <li><strong>Google reviews:</strong> 12 (4.5 stars)</li>
            <li><strong>Time on admin/booking:</strong> 2+ hours daily</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly revenue:</strong> Highly inconsistent ($4K-9K)</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            "I got into detailing because I love making cars look amazing. Instead, I was spending half my time as a secretary, chasing people who didn't show up."
          </p>

          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 my-8">
            <p class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">The Real Cost of No-Shows</p>
            <p class="text-red-800 mb-0">
              "One Friday, I drove 45 minutes to a condo in Oakville for a $400 full detail. Nobody home. No answer to calls or texts. That's gas, toll roads, and half a day lost—not to mention I turned down another booking to take that one."
            </p>
            <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-2 mb-0">— Jason Torres, Owner</p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">The Solution</h2>

          <p>
            We implemented a complete GoHighLevel system designed specifically for mobile detailing operations:
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1. Online Booking with Deposits</h3>

          <p>
            No more text-based scheduling. Customers now book directly through a professional booking page:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>Clear service packages with transparent pricing</li>
            <li>Vehicle size selection (affects price and time)</li>
            <li>Service area verification (postal code check)</li>
            <li>$50 deposit required to confirm (applied to service)</li>
            <li>Automatic calendar sync</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            The deposit alone transformed booking behavior. "When people have skin in the game, they show up," Jason says.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2. Smart Reminder Sequence</h3>

          <p>
            Automated reminders ensure customers don't forget:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>48 hours before:</strong> Confirmation with service details and address verification</li>
            <li><strong>24 hours before:</strong> Reminder with preparation checklist (move car outside, clear garage space, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>2 hours before:</strong> "On my way!" notification with ETA</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            Each message includes a one-click reschedule option—making it easier to move the appointment than to ghost.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">3. Post-Service Review Engine</h3>

          <p>
            After every detail:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Immediately:</strong> Thank you message with before/after photos</li>
            <li><strong>2 hours later:</strong> Review request with Google link</li>
            <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> Follow-up if no review</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            The before/after photos are key—they remind the customer of the transformation and prime them for a positive review.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">4. Automatic Rebooking Reminders</h3>

          <p>
            The biggest game-changer for repeat business:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>4 weeks after interior detail:</strong> "Your interior is probably ready for a refresh"</li>
            <li><strong>6 weeks after full detail:</strong> "Keep your paint protection fresh"</li>
            <li><strong>Quarterly:</strong> Seasonal promotion (winter salt removal, summer road trip prep)</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            Each message includes a one-click rebooking link.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">The Results</h2>

          <p>
            After 5 months, Jason's business is unrecognizable:
          </p>

          <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
            <table class="min-w-full">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b-2 border-slate-300">
                  <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4">Metric</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-3 px-4">Before</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-3 px-4">After</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-3 pl-4">Change</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">No-Show Rate</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">23%</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">4%</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">-82%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Repeat Customer Rate</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">18%</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">45%</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">+150%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Google Reviews</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">12</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">67</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">+458%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Google Rating</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">4.5 stars</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">4.9 stars</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">+0.4</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Time on Admin</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">2+ hours/day</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">15 mins/day</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">-88%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Monthly Revenue</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">$4K-9K</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">$12K-14K</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">+65%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Booking Lead Time</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">1-2 days</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">2 weeks</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">Waitlist</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">The Waitlist Effect</h3>

          <p>
            The most surprising outcome: Jason now has a consistent 2-week booking lead time. His calendar fills up automatically through the rebooking system and Google visibility from reviews.
          </p>

          <p>
            "I used to check my phone constantly hoping for bookings. Now I check my calendar and it's already full. I actually have to be careful not to overbook," Jason laughs.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">The Best Part: More Time Detailing</h2>

          <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 my-8">
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 italic mb-4">
              "I went from spending 2 hours a day texting people to 15 minutes checking my dashboard. That's 10+ hours a week I got back. And I'm not stressed about where my next booking is coming from—the system handles it."
            </p>
            <cite class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 not-italic">— Jason Torres, Owner, Pristine Detail Co.</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">What's Next</h2>

          <p>
            With his schedule consistently full, Jason is now planning for growth:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>Hiring a second detailer (already in training)</li>
            <li>Expanding service area to Oakville and Burlington</li>
            <li>Adding a membership program for recurring revenue</li>
            <li>Considering a physical shop for ceramic coating work</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-8">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">What Made This Work:</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3 mb-0">
              <li><strong>Deposits prevent no-shows:</strong> When customers have money on the line, they show up</li>
              <li><strong>Automated reminders eliminate forgetfulness:</strong> Multiple touchpoints ensure customers don't forget</li>
              <li><strong>Easy rebooking drives repeat business:</strong> One-click rebooking removes all friction</li>
              <li><strong>Review requests at peak satisfaction:</strong> Before/after photos prime positive reviews</li>
              <li><strong>Time saved = revenue gained:</strong> Hours back in the day means more details completed</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- CTA Box -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-cyan-600 p-8 rounded-xl text-white my-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Ready to Transform Your Detailing Business?</h3>
            <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6">
              Get a free consultation and see how we can implement similar results for your operation.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center bg-white text-blue-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
              Book Your Free Demo
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-12">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <a href="/blog/detailing-marketing-guide-canada" class="group block bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-sm text-blue-600 font-medium mb-2">Guide</div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 transition">Complete Guide to Growing Your Detailing Business</h4>
          </a>
          <a href="/industries/auto-services/detailing" class="group block bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
            <div class="text-sm text-blue-600 font-medium mb-2">Service Page</div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 transition">Auto Detailing Marketing Solutions</h4>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
